Dissidents Fleeing Russia
		
			
		
	Get Chilly Welcome in West
AMSTERDAM—A Russian missile designer named Alexander Dolmatov sat down with Dutch immigration officials here last summer and told them he feared for his life.
His former boss at a secretive Russian weapons plant wanted him dead, he claimed, according to a transcript of the meeting. Russian police were hunting for him in Moscow, he said—they had recently visited his mother there—because of his outspoken criticisms of the Kremlin.